            <p facs="#facs_21_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>-490-
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>Democrats in Hamburg have asked themselves: Do we need a theological faculty in the context
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>of the life of the Gniversity? I would say Yes. l would say: it shouldn’t be Two things, but it
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>should be a THIRD thing. The theological faculty should not rule, in the university. The position of
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>the Queen is an impossible one, because from none of these three dimensions of truth can
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>you rule the two others. This is the first and perhaps most important thing about it.
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>secondly, you should notBissolve the theological into a philosophical faculty — That
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>teach in it history, psychology, society, but not THEOlogy! This is
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>means,
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>the OPPOSITE mistake to the "queen," because then the Queen is the philosophical faculty,
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>or humanities—however you call it—which is THEN alleive! But it cannot be decisive. But its
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>dimension of truth is determined mostly by the second level.
               <lb facs="#facs_21_tr_1_tl_13" n="N013"/>But now, which is the POSITIVE meaning of the theological faculty? First a very
            </p>
